title: Entire house
description: Stripped down style, oriental and Mediterranean decoration. Quiet area near the Gammarth forest. 10 mins by car from the beach and shopping areas. 25 minutes from the airport and the medina of Tunis. Friendly and caring welcome. Guaranteed discretion. The hostess is very caring.!

title: Barricade
description: By car : 7 min from the beach, 17 min from the airport, close to bars restaurants coffee shops. From the outside this house looks gorgeous. It has been built with wheat colored bricks and has marble decorations. Small, octagon windows let in plenty of light and have been added to the house in a very symmetric way.

title: The cozy house
description: 2 guests · 1 bedroom · 1 bed · 1 bath. The two extensions are linked by stylish gardens circling around half the house. The second floor is the same size as the first, but part of it hangs over the edge of the floor below, creating an overhang on one side and a balcony on the other. This floor has a very different style than the floor below.

title: Painting house
description: 2 guests · Studio · 1 bed · 1 bath The house is equipped with a large kitchen and one modern bathroom, it also has a cozy living room, four bedrooms, a roomy dining area, a playroom and a spacious garage

feedBack.text: The room here is very clean and the host is very nice. It will always be helpful to you. The location of the room is also very good, very beautiful, just like the photos. In the room you will see the beautiful sea, and if I come to Tunisia next time, I will definitely stay here.

title: Blue villa
description: 16 guests · 6 bedrooms · 16 beds · 2 baths A villa 5 minutes walk from the beach The roof is low and square shaped and is covered with seagrass. One small chimney sits at the side of the house. A few large windows let in just enough light to the rooms below the roof.

feedBack.text: Very nice host near and very nice place to stay in. It is close to Tunis airport and to many shops, cafes and restaurants

title: Accommodation in rafraf beach
description: 1 guest · Studio · 1 bed · 1 private bath . From the outside this house looks gorgeous. It has been built with wheat colored bricks and has marble decorations. Small, octagon windows let in plenty of light and have been added to the house in a very symmetric way.

feedBack.text: Honestly it was lot better than what I expected. It was close to everything and restaurants are less than a minute away. I had my privacy. It was 10mins walk to the medina, and close to the metro too. I stayed for 12days so the washing machine was very useful. Fully working stove, I cooked at home sometimes. Checkin and checkout was hassle free, even though I spoke no Arabic or French. One day I locked myself out and Mohamed was very kind to come to open the door for me. He is a proper gentleman. I will definitely recommend his place, and I will stay again
